---
import Base from '~/layouts/Base.astro';
import Header from '~/components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '~/components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE } from '~/data/site';
---

<Base title="Privacy" description="Privacy policy for Magic Term — what we collect (almost nothing) and what we never share.">
  <Header />
  <main class="legal">
    <header class="legal__head">
      <h1>Privacy</h1>
      <p>What we collect (almost nothing) and what we never share.</p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2>The desktop app</h2>
      <p>
        Magic Term has <strong>zero telemetry</strong>. The app does not phone home, does not collect
        analytics, does not report errors automatically. The only outgoing traffic is:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Your own SSH/SFTP servers</strong> — encrypted with the SSH protocol.</li>
        <li><strong>Supabase</strong> — Magic Term currently requires an account, and your encrypted
          vault is synced through Supabase. Your credentials are end-to-end encrypted on your device
          before they're sent. Supabase only ever sees ciphertext, a salted scrypt verifier of your
          master password, and metadata you choose to share with your team. A fully-local mode
          (no account, no sync) is on the roadmap.</li>
        <li><strong>GitHub Releases</strong> — the auto-updater pings the public releases endpoint
          to check for new versions. No identifiers are sent.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>This website</h2>
      <p>
        We use <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> on this site. It's a privacy-friendly,
        cookie-free analytics product that aggregates anonymous traffic statistics — page views,
        referrers, and country codes — without setting any cookies or persisting individual
        identifiers.
      </p>
      <p>
        We do not use Google Analytics. We do not load tracking pixels. We do not sell, share,
        or correlate visitor data with any third party.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>What's stored in the cloud</h2>
      <p>
        When you create an account, the following is stored on Supabase:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your email and a Supabase auth token.</li>
        <li>An <strong>encrypted</strong> blob containing your servers, snippets, and settings. We can't
          decrypt it — that requires your master password, which never leaves your machine.</li>
        <li>A <strong>scrypt verifier</strong> of your master password. We can't reverse it to your password.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Sign out at any time to wipe local credentials. Delete your account in Settings to remove
        all server-side data.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Open source</h2>
      <p>
        Don't take our word for it. The entire client and server schema are public:
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href={SITE.githubUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">{SITE.githubUrl}</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <p class="legal__date">Last updated: May 2026</p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 80px 24px 0;
  }

  .legal__head {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .legal__head h1 {
    font-size: clamp(36px, 6vw, 56px);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--fg);
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }

  .legal__head p {
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 18px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  section { margin-bottom: 32px; }

  h2 {
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--fg);
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }

  p {
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }

  ul {
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }

  li { margin-bottom: 6px; }

  strong {
    color: var(--fg);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  a:hover { color: var(--accent-hover); }

  .legal__date {
    color: var(--fg-subtle);
    font-size: 13px;
    margin-top: 64px;
  }
</style>
